The paper deals with resource allocation in a wireless network, specifically LTE in the unlicensed band, with uplink-downlink decoupling. This falls under the domain of networked systems and communication in computer science. The use of machine learning algorithms, specifically echo state networks, for self-organizing resource allocation suggests a focus on neural networks and learning in computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
